"June 19, 2020. Estonia announced relaxed restrictions for schools, but the following measures remain:
1) the scattering of people is ensured;
2) there are up to ten persons in a study group, except for examinations;
3) when organizing examinations, students taking an examination are scattered in the examination room;
4) movements of groups of students in the building of the relevant educational institution and in the territory used for the provision of education are scattered;
5) shared items in the building of the relevant educational institution and in the territory used for the provision of education are disinfected after use."

